We employed the Planck’s law of black body radiation to explore the physicochemical characteristics of thermal radiation. This physicochemical principle illustrates the spectral density of electromagnetic radiation emitted from a black body that remains in thermal equilibrium with its environment at a specific temperature. According to Planck’s law, the spectral energy density ρT (λ) of thermal radiation is given byρT(λ)=8πhcλ51ehc/λkBT−1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
