To examine whether the Pfr-to-Pr dark conversion can be explained by IR responsiveness, we employed a model of Pfr kinetics. The phytochrome photoconversion is affected by the extinction coefficient (ε) of the pigment (chromophore) and the quantum yield (ϕ) of the process, where the photoconversion cross-section (σ) of the pigment is given by 2.3 × ε ϕ12. In a phytochrome solution exposed to a thermal radiation of photon flux Nλ, the rate of change in [Pfr] is given as follows:d[Pfr]dt=NRσR[Pr]−NFRσFR[Pfr]−NIRkIR[Pfr]\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
